comments: Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Conley's (UTA) path and does not deliver the contact.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) rolls out of his screening position and makes a natural move toward the lane, and he and Conley (UTA) briefly engage and disengage.
Gobert (UTA) maintains legal guarding position as contact is made with Morant (MEM) at the end of the drive.
Conley (UTA) makes marginal contact with Brooks' (MEM) front that does not affect his FOM in the lane.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) makes marginal contact with Mitchell's (UTA) right side after completing the hand-off.
Brooks (MEM) places his arm on Gobert's (UTA) midsection and slides it off without affecting his FOM.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Brooks' (MEM) path and does not deliver the contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) engages with Gobert (UTA) after the release of the jump shot attempt and disengages without affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Bogdanovic (UTA) maintains legal guarding position as body contact is made with Morant (MEM) during the drive.
O'Neale (UTA) makes marginal body contact with Jackson Jr. (MEM) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) engages with Valanciunas (MEM) during the rebound but does not deliver contact.
Gobert (UTA) has his arms positioned outside the frame of his body and makes contact with Brooks (MEM), but the contact is marginal.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) initiates contact with Gobert (UTA) that affects his ability to catch the pass.
Mitchell (UTA) makes marginal contact with Brooks' (MEM) front that does not affect Brooks' SQBR as he attempts to defend over the pick.
Valanciunas (MEM) makes marginal contact with Gobert's (UTA) backside after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Valanciunas (MEM) engages and disengages with Gobert (UTA) without affecting his FOM.
Crowder (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and does not deliver the contact.
Bogdanovic (UTA) maintains legal guarding position as contact is made with Morant (MEM) in the lane.
Morant (MEM) does not bring his hand underneath the ball and bring it to a pause during his dribble.
Gobert (UTA) cleanly blocks Morant's (MEM) shot attempt while it is on its upward trajectory and before it reaches its apex.

The shot clock is turned off when O'Neale (UTA) gains possession of the ball, but he fumbles it as he attempts to call a timeout.  O'Neale is then awarded the timeout when he regains possession of the ball at the 00:02.8 mark.
Conley (UTA) continues moving into Crowder (MEM) after initial contact takes place, but the ensuing contact is marginal and does not affect Crowder's ability to defend.
Anderson (MEM) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM.
Brooks (MEM) and Mitchell (UTA) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM.
Hill (MEM) makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with Mitchell's (UTA) hand that is considered part of the ball during his upward shooting motion.
